# HMAC-SHA256 in JavaScript in Browser
created: undefined, last updated: 2026-06-10, [Read more](https://mojoauth.com/hashing/hmac-sha256-in-javascript-in-browser)

To implement HMAC-SHA256 in JavaScript within a browser, the Web Crypto API is the recommended approach.
Below is a simple example demonstrating how to generate an HMAC-SHA256 signature.
```
async function generateHMAC(key, message) {
// Encode the key and message as Uint8Array
const encoder = new TextEncoder();
const keyData = encoder.encode(key);
const messageData = encoder.encode(message);
// Import the key
const cryptoKey = await window.crypto.subtle.importKey(
'raw',
keyData,
{ name: 'HMAC', hash: { name: 'SHA-256' } },
false,
['sign']
);
// Generate HMAC
const signature = await window.crypto.subtle.sign(
'HMAC',
cryptoKey,
messageData
);
// Convert signature to hex format
return Array.from(new Uint8Array(signature)).map(b => ('00' + b.toString(16)).slice(-2)).join('');
// Usage example
generateHMAC('mySecretKey', 'Hello, World!').then(signature => {
console.log('HMAC-SHA256 Signature:', signature);
});
...
```
